Hyletic, Hyletics: As used by Husserl, means "the analysis of matter (hyle) - or raw impressions - of an intentional act, such as perception, abstracting from the form (morphe) that animates it and confers meaning on it." (See Paul Ricoeur, "Time and Narrative", University of Chicago Press, 1988; endnote 4, p. 281)